name: enaR
tagline: enaR = Ecological Network Analysis in R
body:
enaR is a tool box for Ecological Network Analysis built in R. 

To start using enaR, open R and run:

```
> install.packages('enaR')
> library('enaR')
> vignette('enaR')
```

### GitHub

You can also download the source code for the most recent version from GitHub from right here (see links to the "tar.gz" file).

### Authors and Contributors

The vast majority of this work has been done at the SEE Lab at UNCW.

[S.R. Borrett](http://people.uncw.edu/borretts/people.html) = code overlord.

[M.K. Lau](http://dana.ucc.nau.edu/~mkl48/bio/home.html) = R junky.

[D.E. Hines](http://people.uncw.edu/borretts/people.html) = master of Ascendency.

### Support or Contact

If you would like to contribute or you have helpful suggestions or questions, please contact Matt or Stuart at enaR.maintainer@gmail.com.
